eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable

Class ImmutableMapWrapper<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable.ImmutableMapWrapper<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the map's key type
    V - the map's elements type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImmutableMap<K,V>, java.io.Serializable

    public class ImmutableMapWrapper<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ImmutableMap<K,V>
    An implementation of ImmutableMap. The implementation wraps a java.util.Map, such that the user who has this object can change nothing in the map. However - the one who has the original java.util.Map, can change the map - and the changes will take effect on this map as well.
    Author:
    Asher Stern

        public java.util.Map<K,V> getMutableCopy()
        Description copied from interface: ImmutableMap
        Returns a mutable copy of the map. That copy is hard copy. Changing it does not change the original map.

        There is no guarantee about the returned map's type. It is only known that it implements java.util.Map
